.TH "BEEHIIV-SUBSCRIPTIONS-DELETE" "1" "Apr 2026" "beehiiv-cli" "Beehiiv CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
beehiiv-subscriptions-delete - Delete a subscription by ID


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbeehiiv subscriptions delete  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete subscription

.PP
This cannot be undone. All data associated with the subscription will also be deleted. We recommend unsubscribing when possible instead of deleting. If a premium subscription is deleted they will no longer be billed. Deletes a subscription.

.PP
API path: /publications/{publicationId}/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for delete

.PP
\fB--query\fP=[]
	Add a repeatable query parameter in key=value form


